msgid ""
"This is a large-scale map, where you may choose a way to go. Move Gawen to a "
"signpost or any other location to move to a new scenario. Move Gawen to the "
"tent to talk with his friends."
msgstr ""
"Questa è una mappa su grande scala, dove potrai scegliere dove andare. Devi "
"spostare Gawen verso un cartello o in qualunque altra posizione per "
"cominciare a muoverti verso il prossimo scenario. Sposta Gawen verso la "
"tenda per discutere con i suoi amici."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:459
msgid ""
"My lord, we cannot go back to Freetown. We have nothing to report, and we "
"have not found anything about the orcs."
msgstr ""
"Mio signore, non possiamo andare di nuovo a Freetown. Non abbiamo niente da "
"riferire e non abbiamo scoperto ancora nulla sugli orchi."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:462
msgid ""
"My lord, I do not think we should go back to Freetown already. We haven't "
"met with the She-wolf of Haeltin west of here. She may have some great "
"insight, having fought with orcs already."
msgstr ""
"Mio signore, non penso che dovremmo già tornare di nuovo a Freetown. Non "
"abbiamo ancora incontrato quella Lupa di Haeltin a est di qui. Forse sa "
"qualcosa, avendo combattuto con gli orchi."

#. [then]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:476
msgid "We were in Haeltin already. Where would you like to go now?"
msgstr "Siamo già a Haeltin. Dove andiamo adesso?"

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:480
msgid "Are you sure you want to go there?"
msgstr "Sei sicuro di volerci andare?"

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:486
msgid "As you wish, my lord."
msgstr "Come desideri, mio signore."

#. [then]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:500
msgid "We already were in Saorduc. Where to now?"
msgstr "Siamo già a Saorduc. Dove andiamo adesso?"

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:504
msgid ""
"Are you sure you want to go there? I've told you that I doubt Saurians know "
"anything useful."
msgstr ""
"Sei sicuro di volerci andare? Ti ho già detto che dubito che i Sauri "
"sappiano qualcosa di utile."

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:509
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:511
msgid ""
"So, on to Saorduc! Hopefully it is a wise decision and lizard men know "
"something about orcs."
msgstr ""
"A Saorduc dunque! Speriamo che sia una saggia decisione e che le lucertole "
"sappiano qualcosa degli orchi."

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:515
msgid "Lizards? We already fought with them. I hate lizards."
msgstr "Lucertole? Ci abbiamo già combattuto. Odio le lucertole."

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:520
msgid "That was wise decision, my lord."
msgstr "È stata una saggia decisione, mio signore."

#. [then]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:536
msgid "We already scouted near Barnon. Where should we go now?"
msgstr "Siamo già stati in ricognizione vicino a Barnon. Dobbiamo andarci ora?"

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:540
msgid ""
"Are you sure you want to go there? A lot of enemy soldiers could be near "
"Barnon."
msgstr ""
"Sei sicuro di volerci andare? Ci potrebbe essere un mucchio di nemici vicino "
"a Barnon."

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:544
msgid ""
"This could be dangerous... but also extremely valuable. We can definitely "
"find out something about orcs there."
msgstr ""
"Potrebbe essere pericoloso. Ma anche estremamente importante. Sicuramente "
"possiamo scoprire qualcosa sugli orchi là."

#. [else]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:547
msgid "Yes, on other hand, maybe we should search elsewhere."
msgstr "Sì, d'altra parte forse dovremmo cercare altrove."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:557
msgid "Who is comin' here? What d'ya wanna from us?"
msgstr "Chi sta arrivando? Che volete da noi?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:558
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:597
msgid "Don't be afraid, I want ask you few question and then I will go."
msgstr "Non aver paura, vorrei solo farti qualche domanda e poi me ne andrò."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:559
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "So go on an' ask us"
msgid "So go on an' ask us, then."
msgstr "Avanti, chiedi."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:565
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:603
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:636
msgid "Do you know where the place called Bontom is?"
msgstr "Sai dove si trova il luogo chiamato Bontom?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:566
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:578
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:604
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:616
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:637
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:649
msgid "Do you know anything about Reme Carrenemoe?"
msgstr "Hai notizie di Reme Carrenemoe?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:567
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:579
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:605
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:617
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:638
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:650
msgid "Have you heard anything about orcs?"
msgstr "Hai sentito qualcosa degli orchi?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:568
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:580
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:606
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:618
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:639
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:651
msgid "Would you want to fight for me?"
msgstr "Vuoi combattere per me?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:569
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:581
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:607
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:619
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:640
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:652
msgid "Go and work, good man."
msgstr "Va' a lavorare, buon uomo."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:592
msgid "Ah, welcome, we've heard about your victories, Gaumhaldric."
msgstr "Ah, benvenuto, ci è giunta notizia delle vostre vittorie, Gaumhaldric."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:594
msgid "I still can't get used to them calling him Gaumhaldric."
msgstr "Non mi sono ancora abituato a essere chiamato Gaumhaldric."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:595
msgid "Cute name, isn't it?"
msgstr "Bel nome, vero?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:598
msgid "Anything for you, young knight."
msgstr "Per te qualsiasi cosa, giovane cavaliere."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:631
msgid "Free men from Raedwood forest! You are always welcome here."
msgstr "Uomini liberi della foresta di Raedwood! Qua siete sempre i benvenuti."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:673
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:682
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Majid Yahyazad"
msgid "Yahyazad"
msgstr "Majid Yahyazad"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:709
msgid "Where Reme Carrenemoe could possibly be?"
msgstr "Dove potrebbe essere Reme Carrenemoe?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:710
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/18_Start_of_the_Quest.cfg:576
msgid "Advise me what could we do now."
msgstr "Consigliami cosa potremmo fare ora."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:711
msgid "Tell me about my mother."
msgstr "Dimmi di mia madre."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:716
msgid "You are joking, right? He is in our camp!"
msgstr "Stai scherzando, vero? È dalla nostra parte."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:718
msgid "Probably still in that Bontom place the peasants told us about."
msgstr "Probabilmente in quel Bontom di cui ci hanno detto i contadini."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:720
msgid "In some place called Bontom. We could ask peasants about it."
msgstr ""
"In un certo posto chiamato Bontom. Potremmo chiedere ai contadini a questo "
"proposito."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:722
msgid "I have no idea where your friend may be."
msgstr "Non ho idea di dove possa essere il nostro amico."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:729
msgid "About your mother? What do you want to know about her?"
msgstr "Di tua madre? Cosa vuoi sapere di lei?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:730
msgid "Everything."
msgstr "Tutto."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:731
msgid ""
"Well, she was from a royal house. The Akladian king gave her a simple "
"choice: marry him or he would unleash his anger on her family. So, she "
"agreed. I visited her from time to time, singing songs, bringing her news "
"from home... "
msgstr ""
"Be', apparteneva alla casa reale. Il re di Akladia le ha proposto una "
"semplice scelta: avrebbe dovuto sposarlo altrimenti avrebbe scatenato la sua "
"furia sulla sua famiglia. Così, ha dovuto accettare quella proposta. Di "
"tanto in tanto le facevo visita, per cantarle delle canzoni, raccontarle le "
"notizie di casa..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:732
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I think eventually she even warmed to your father, the king. When she "
#| "gave birth to you, she gave everything she had for you. But behind her "
#| "back Akladian clans were conspiring... and finally someone gave her a "
#| "poisoned cup. She died, slowly, and painfully. I was able to be near her "
#| "in her final hours. I promised her that I would take care of you."
msgid ""
"I think eventually she even warmed up to your father, the king. When she "
"gave birth to you, she gave everything she had for you. But behind her back "
"Akladian clans were conspiring... and finally someone gave her a poisoned "
"cup. She died, slowly, and painfully. I was able to be near her in her final "
"hours. I promised her that I would take care of you."
msgstr ""
"Penso che cominciasse persino a piacerle quel re, vostro padre. Quando vi "
"diede alla luce, si è dedicata completamente a voi. Ma alle sue spalle i "
"clan di Akladia stavano cospirando... e alla fine qualcuno le diede una "
"coppa avvelenata. Morì, morì lentamente. Ero riuscito a starle vicino fino "
"all'ultimo. Le promisi di prendermi cura di te."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:733
msgid "Who poisoned her?"
msgstr "Chi l'ha avvelenata?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:734
msgid "I don't know. No one knows."
msgstr "Non lo so. Nessuno lo sa."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:736
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Rob Roe mentioned Lorin clan once bought some special poison from "
#| "Outlaws... "
msgid ""
"Rob Roe mentioned Lorin's clan once bought some special poison from "
"Outlaws... "
msgstr ""
"Una volta Rob Roe menzionò il clan di Lorin che una volta comprò un certo "
"veleno speciale dai Senzalegge..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:737
msgid "And you think that..."
msgstr "E tu pensi che..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:738
msgid "Why shouldn't I think that?"
msgstr "Perché dovrei pensarlo?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:739
msgid ""
"You are right, Gawen. Akladians have a long history of poisoning each other. "
"You might say it's their national sport. But still... yes, it had escaped my "
"attention before."
msgstr ""
"Hai ragione, Gawen. La gente di Akladia si avvelena costantemente l'un "
"l'altro. Si potrebbe dire che sia il loro sport nazionale. Ma ancora... sì, "
"mi era uscito di mente."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:744
msgid "Hey Karen, what's up?"
msgstr "Ehi Karen, come va?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:745
msgid "I just made up a new song about you, want to hear it?"
msgstr "Ho appena finito di scrivere una nuova canzona, la vuoi sentire?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:746
msgid "You are a gifted girl... fighting, singing, what else can you do?"
msgstr "Hai del talento ragazza, combatti, canti, cos'altro sai fare?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:747
msgid ""
"I can also dance. Gawen. When we return to Freetown I could dance for you... "
msgstr ""
"So anche ballare. Gawen, quando torneremo a Freetown potrei ballare per te."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:748
msgid "I'm sure I would enjoy watching you dance."
msgstr "Sono certo che sarà un bello spettacolo."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:749
msgid "Oh, I bet you would!"
msgstr "Ci puoi scommettere!"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:751
msgid ""
"Thank you, Gawen, once again. You have saved my life. I will never forget "
"it, and I will never be able to repay my debt. Earlier my life belonged to "
"you because of duty; now it is yours by choice."
msgstr ""
"Grazie una volta ancora Gawen. Mi hai salvato la vita. Non me ne "
"dimenticherò mai e io non potrò mai ripagare questo mio debito. Finora la "
"mia vita ti apparteneva per dovere; ora ti appartiene per mia scelta."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:753
msgid "Gaumhaldric, an interesting mother you have. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""
"Ehi Gaumhaldric, tua madre è una donna affascinante. Ti posso fare una "
"domanda?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:754
msgid "Sure, go ahead."
msgstr "Certo, dimmi."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:755
msgid ""
"Is she spoken for? I mean, is there someone she loves? I have often noticed "
"her gazing up at the sky, far, far away, as if she were thinking about "
"someone... or something."
msgstr ""
"È impegnata? Voglio dire, ama qualcuno? Ho notato che a volte volge lo "
"sguardo al cielo, lontano, lontano come se stesse pensando a qualcuno... o a "
"qualcosa."

#. [event]
#. this is just Gawen's assumption; my own assumption is that she is thinking about what the Oracle told her:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:757
msgid ""
"I think she must be remembering my father. She has no one else I know about."
msgstr "Penso che ripensi a mio padre. Non ha nessun altro che io sappia."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:758
msgid ""
"That is fortunate for me. She seems to have locked her heart up in an "
"unbreakable fortress... but I think I can find a way into her heart. With "
"time and patience, I'm sure I can discover a way to break down those walls. "
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:759
msgid ""
"Majid Yahyazad, Lorin is my step-mother, but she has never really shown any "
"tenderness, even to me. I have always known her to be a harsh and "
"unforgiving woman."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:760
msgid ""
"I'm afraid pursuing her will come with a heavy price. I think she thinks "
"love is a weakness... she seems more interested in war and finding new ways "
"to cause pain to others."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:761
msgid ""
"Ah, Gaumhaldric, perhaps you are right, but if it will be as a war to unlock "
"her heart, I am prepared to wage it. I am well-acquainted with the ways of "
"war."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:762
msgid ""
"Besides, in the end, the war for the affection of a worthy woman is the only "
"war where the price to win is a privilege, not a burden, to pay."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:763
msgid "You find my step-mother... a worthy challenge, then? "
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:764
msgid "I do... and shall gladly pay the price to try to win her heart. "
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:765
msgid ""
"You have my blessing, noble Majid, for what it's worth. Sometimes the "
"ruthlessness of the 'She-Wolf of Haeltin' still scares even me. "
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:770
msgid "Mother, may I have a word with you?"
msgstr "Madre, posso dirti una cosa?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:771
msgid "Your clan once bought poison from outlaws. Why?"
msgstr "Il tuo clan ha procurato del veleno da Senzalegge. Perché?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:772
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:780
msgid "What do you think about Yahyazad?"
msgstr "Che ne pensi di Yahyazad?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:773
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:781
msgid "What do you know about orcs?"
msgstr "Cosa sai degli orchi?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:774
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:782
msgid "How did my real mother die?"
msgstr "Come è morta mia madre?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:788
msgid "Why do you ask?"
msgstr "Perché lo chiedi?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:789
msgid "Well, he seems to be interested in you."
msgstr "Be', pare che sia interessato a te."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:790
msgid ""
"Yes, I noticed that. I think one would have to be blind NOT to notice that. "
"But I am not interested in him."
msgstr ""
"Sì, l'ho notato. Penso che solo un cieco non lo noterebbe. Ma lui non mi "
"interessa."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:791
msgid "Why not? He seems to be a good man."
msgstr "Perché? È un bel ragazzo."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:792
msgid "He is an underling."
msgstr "È un miserabile."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:793
msgid ""
"Underling? Mother, why do you still use such words? I am 'underling' too, "
"after all."
msgstr ""
"Un miserabile? Madre, perché usi questo termine? Anche io sono un "
"miserabile, dopo tutto."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:794
msgid ""
"No! I could never call you that. You are not... I mean... I... oh, you are "
"too young to understand!"
msgstr ""
"No! Non devi mai dire una cosa del genere. Tu non sei... voglio dire... Ah, "
"sei troppo giovane per capire."

#. [event]
#. cross-reference to dialogue in S16, Choosing the Best:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:796
msgid ""
"Besides, you have lost your memory, so you probably do not remember what our "
"customs are regarding widows that betray their dead husbands. I will explain "
"it to you another time."
msgstr ""
"Inoltre, hai perso la memoria al punto che forse non ti ricordi neanche "
"quali sono le nostre tradizioni sulle vedove, che tradiscono il proprio "
"marito defunto. Te le spiegherò più tardi."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:798
msgid ""
"Orcs? They are good fighters. Strong, disciplined, I wish I had such "
"soldiers."
msgstr ""
"Orchi: sono buoni guerrieri. Forti, disciplinati, ne avessi di soldati così."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:799
msgid ""
"Mother, orcs just burn, pillage, and murder! They hate us, and yet you seem "
"to respect them?!?"
msgstr ""
"Madre, gli orchi incendiano, fanno razzie, assassinano, ci odiano e tu "
"sembri rispettarli?!?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:800
msgid ""
"Well, we are burning, pillaging, murdering and hate our enemies too. What's "
"the difference?"
msgstr ""
"Beh, anche noi incendiamo, razziamo, assassiniamo e odiamo i nostro nemici. "
"E allora?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:802
msgid "Poison? What poison? My clan has never bought any poison!"
msgstr "Veleno? Quale veleno? Il mio clan non ha mai comprato nessun veleno."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:803
msgid "Rob Roe told me about it."
msgstr "Me lo ha detto Rob Roe."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:804
msgid ""
"Can you repeat that name? Rob - Roe. Rob Roe... No, I can't say I remember "
"that name. I don't know anything about my clan buying a poison. But then, I "
"am only a woman, and our clan lord didn't tell me everything."
msgstr ""
"Puoi ripetere quel nome? Rob - Roe. Rob Roe. No, questo nome non me lo "
"ricordo. Uhm.. Be', non so nulla del fatto che il mio clan abbia comprato un "
"veleno. Sono solo una donna, il signore del clan non mi raccontava tutto."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:807
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Your mother? Your.. why you are asking ME about your mother?"
msgid "Your mother? Your... why you are asking ME about your mother?"
msgstr "Tua madre? Tua... perché chiedi a ME di tua madre?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:808
msgid ""
"I can't remember anything about her. I would love to hear something about "
"her. Did you know her?"
msgstr ""
"Di lei non ricordo nulla. Mi piacerebbe sapere qualcosa di lei. L'hai "
"conosciuta?"

#. [event]
#. this is a Suspiciously Specific Denial: https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuspiciouslySpecificDenial
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:810
msgid ""
"No! I did not know her! I... I'm sorry Gawen, but I don't know how your "
"mother died or who poisoned her."
msgstr ""
"No! Non l'ho conosciuta! Mi... mi spiace, Gawen, ma non so come tua madre è "
"morta né chi l'ha avvelenata."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:811
msgid "I wasn't asking you about that."
msgstr "Non ti ho chiesto questo."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:828
msgid "There are no more orcs near this ruins of the village."
msgstr "Non ci sono più orchi attorno alle rovine del villaggio."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:831
msgid ""
"My lord! This time for sure you will chase off that orcish band, kill all "
"the orcs, and free my people!"
msgstr ""
"Mio signore! È sicuramente il momento propizio per inseguire quella banda di "
"orchi, ucciderli tutti e liberare la mia gente!"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:833
msgid "So, should we take on the orcs?"
msgstr "Così, dovremmo occuparci di quegli orchi?"

#. [unit]: type=Peasant, id=Matthews Eagle Eye
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:845
msgid "Matthews Eagle Eye"
msgstr "Matthews \"occhio di falco\""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:854
msgid "Someone is hiding here!"
msgstr "Qualcuno si è nascosto qui!"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:856
msgid "Ah! Humans! And Akladians with them?! Still, what good fortune!"
msgstr "Ah! Uomini! e gente di Akladia con loro?! Ma che bella notizia!"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:858
msgid "Ah! Humans! And not Akladians! What good fortune!"
msgstr "Ah! Uomini! e nessuna gente di Akladia! Ma che bella notizia!"

#. [event]
